data.name: Grookey
data.flavorText: When it uses its special stick to strike up a beat, the sound waves produced carry revitalizing energy to the plants and flowers in the area.

data.name: Scorbunny
data.flavorText: A warm-up of running around gets fire energy coursing through this Pokémon's body. Once that happens, it's ready to fight at full power.

data.name: Sobble
data.flavorText: When scared, this Pokémon cries. Its tears pack the chemical punch of 100 onions, and attackers won't be able to resist weeping.

data.name: Rillaboom
data.flavorText: By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle.

data.name: Frosmoth
data.flavorText: It shows no mercy to any who desecrate fields and mountains. It will fly around on its icy wings, causing a blizzard to chase offenders away.

data.name: Galarian Perrserker
data.flavorText: What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokémon lives for the thrill of battle.

data.name: Cinccino
data.flavorText: Its body secrets oil that this Pokémon spreads over its nest as a coating to protect it from dust. Cinccino won't tolerate even a speck of the stuff.

data.name: Gossifleur
data.flavorText: It anchors itself in the ground with its single leg, then basks in the sun. After absorbing enough sunlight, its petals spread as it blooms brilliantly.

data.name: Wooloo
data.flavorText: Its curly fleece is such an effective cushion that this Pokémon could fall off a cliff and stand right back up at the bottom, unharmed.

data.name: Morpeko
data.flavorText: As it eats the seeds stored up in its pocket-like pouches, this Pokémon is not just satisfying its constant hunger. It's also generating electricity.

data.name: Galarian Ponyta
data.flavorText: Its small horn hides a healing power. With a few rubs from this Pokémon's horn, any slight wound you have will be healed.

data.name: Pikachu
data.flavorText: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

data.name: Flapple
data.flavorText: It ate a sour apple, and that induced its evolution. In its cheeks, it stores an acid capable of causing chemical burns.

data.name: Luxray
data.flavorText: Luxray's ability to see through objects comes in handy when it's scouting for danger.

data.name: Coalossal
data.flavorText: It's usually peaceful, but the vandalism of mines enrages it. Offenders will be incinerated with flames that reach 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit.

data.name: Garbodor
data.flavorText: This Pokémon eats trash, which turns into poison inside its body. The main component of the poison depends on what sort of trash was eaten.

data.name: Mantine
data.flavorText: If it builds up enough speed swimming, it can jump out above the waves and glide for over 300 feet.

data.name: Noctowl
data.flavorText: When it needs to think, it rotates its head 180 degrees to sharpen its intellectual power.

data.name: Duraludon
data.flavorText: Its body resembles polished metal, and it's both lightweight and strong. The only drawback is that it rusts easily.

data.name: Rayquaza
data.flavorText: It flies in the ozone layer, way up high in the sky. Until recently, no one had ever seen it.

data.name: Morpeko
data.flavorText: As it eats the seeds stored up in its pocket-like pouches, this Pokémon is not just satisfying its constant hunger. It's also generating electricity.

data.name: Snorlax
data.flavorText: It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.

data.name: Zacian
data.flavorText: Now armed with a weapon it used in ancient times, this Pokémon needs only a single strike to fell even Gigantamax Pokémon.

data.name: Zamazenta
data.flavorText: Its ability to deflect any attack led to it being known as the Fighting Master's Shield. It was feared and respected by all.

data.name: Decidueye
data.flavorText: As if wielding a bow, it launches the arrow quills hidden among the feathers of its wings. Decidueye's shots never miss.

data.name: Arctozolt
data.flavorText: The shaking of its freezing upper half is what generates its electricity. It has a hard time walking around.

data.name: Hydreigon
data.flavorText: There are a slew of stories about villages that were destroyed by Hydreigon. It bites anything that moves.

data.name: Kangaskhan
data.flavorText: You shouldn't get close to the child when it's playing outside its mother's pouch. Its mother is always nearby watching over it.

data.name: Pikachu
data.flavorText: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

data.name: Hatenna
data.flavorText: Via the protrusion on its head, it senses other creatures' emotions. If you don't have a calm disposition, it will never warm up to you.

data.name: Flareon
data.flavorText: Once it has stored up enough heat, this Pokémon's body temperature can reach up to 1,700 degrees Fahrenheit.

data.name: Eevee
data.flavorText: It has the ability to alter the composition of its body to suit its surrounding environment.

data.name: Eldegoss
data.flavorText: The cotton on the head of this Pokémon can be spun into a glossy, gorgeous yarn—a Galar regional specialty.

data.name: Drednaw
data.flavorText: This Pokémon rapidly extends its retractable neck to sink its sharp fangs into distant enemies and take them down.

data.name: Centiskorch
data.flavorText: When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.

data.name: Lapras
data.flavorText: A smart and kindhearted Pokémon, it glides across the surface of the sea while its beautiful song echoes around it.

data.name: Gengar
data.flavorText: On the night of a full moon, if shadows move on their own and laugh, it must be Gengar's doing.

data.name: Machamp
data.flavorText: It quickly swings its four arms to rock its opponents with ceaseless punches and chops from all angles.

data.name: Coalossal
data.flavorText: It's usually peaceful, but the vandalism of mines enrages it. Offenders will be incinerated with flames that reach 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit.

data.name: Alcremie
data.flavorText: When it trusts a Trainer, it will treat them to berries it's decorated with cream.

data.name: Galarian Obstagoon
data.flavorText: It evolved after experiencing numerous fights. While crossing its arms, it lets out a shout that would make any opponent flinch.

data.name: Duraludon
data.flavorText: Its body resembles polished metal, and it's both lightweight and strong. The only drawback is that it rusts easily.

data.name: Charizard
data.flavorText: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.

data.name: Donphan
data.flavorText: The longer and bigger its tusks, the higher its rank in its herd. The tusks take long to grow.

data.name: Snorlax
data.flavorText: It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.

data.name: Lugia
data.flavorText: It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.

data.name: Grookey
data.flavorText: When it uses its special stick to strike up a beat, the sound waves produced carry revitalizing energy to the plants and flowers in the area.

data.name: Scorbunny
data.flavorText: A warm-up of running around gets fire energy coursing through this Pokémon's body. Once that happens, it's ready to fight at full power.

data.name: Vaporeon
data.flavorText: When Vaporeon's fins begin to vibrate, it is a sign that rain will come within a few hours.

data.name: Sobble
data.flavorText: When scared, this Pokémon cries. Its tears pack the chemical punch of 100 onions, and attacks won't be able to resist weeping.

data.name: Special Delivery Pikachu
data.flavorText: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

data.name: Galarian Mr. Rime
data.flavorText: It's highly skilled at tap-dancing. It waves its cane of ice in time with its graceful movements.

data.name: Dedenne
data.flavorText: Its upper whiskers are sensors that survey its surroundings. Its lower whiskers are organs that shoot electricity.

data.name: Polteageist
data.flavorText: This species lives in antique teapots. Most pots are forgeries, but on rare occasions, an authentic work is found.

data.name: Bunnelby
data.flavorText: It excels at digging holes. Using its ears, it can dig a nest 33 feet deep in one night.

data.name: Cherrim
data.flavorText: The faint scent that emanates from its full blossom entices bug Pokémon to it.

data.name: Octillery
data.flavorText: It traps enemies with its suction-cupped tentacles, then smashes them with its rock-hard head.

data.name: Houndoom
data.flavorText: Identifiable by its eerie howls, people a long time ago thought it was the grim reaper and feared it.

data.name: Bronzong
data.flavorText: Many scientists suspect that this Pokémon originated outside the Galar region, based on the patterns on its body.

data.name: Charmander
data.flavorText: It has a preference for hot things. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

data.name: Arrokuda
data.flavorText: If it sees any movement around it, this Pokémon charges for it straightaway, leading with its sharply pointed jaw. It's very proud of that jaw.

data.name: Jolteon
data.flavorText: If it is angered or startled, the fur all over its body bristles like sharp needles that pierce foes.

data.name: Eevee
data.flavorText: It has the ability to alter the composition of its body to suit its surrounding environment.

data.name: Cinderace
data.flavorText: It's skilled at both offense and defense, and it gets pumped up when cheered on. But if it starts showboating, it could put itself in a tough spot.

data.name: Inteleon
data.flavorText: Its nictitating membranes let it pick out foes' weak points so it can precisely blast them with water that shoots from its fingertips at Mach 3.

data.name: Cresselia
data.flavorText: Those who sleep holding Cresselia's feather are assured of joyful dreams. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

data.name: Passimian
data.flavorText: Passimian live in groups of about 20, with each member performing an assigned role. Through cooperation, the group survives.

data.name: Morpeko
data.flavorText: As it eats the seeds stored up in its pocket-like pouches, this Pokémon is not just satisfying its constant hunger. It's also generating electricity.

data.name: Phanpy
data.flavorText: It is strong despite its compact size. It can easily pick up and carry an adult human on its back.

data.name: Eevee
data.flavorText: It has the ability to alter the composition of its body to suit its surrounding environment.

data.name: Snorlax
data.flavorText: This Pokémon's stomach is so strong, even eating moldy or rotten food will not affect it.

data.name: Umbreon
data.flavorText: On the night of a full moon, or when it gets excited, the ring patterns on its body glow yellow.

data.name: Eevee
data.flavorText: Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokémon conceals many different possible evolutions.

data.name: Galarian Articuno
data.flavorText: Known as Articuno, this Pokémon fires beams that can immobilize opponents as if they had been frozen solid.

data.name: Flaaffy
data.flavorText: It stores electricity in its fluffy fleece. If it stores up too much, it will start to go bald in those patches.

data.name: Eiscue
data.flavorText: This Pokémon keeps its heat-sensitive head cool with ice. It fishes for its food, dangling its single hair into the sea to lure in prey.

data.name: Galarian Moltres
data.flavorText: The sinister aura that blazes like molten fire around this Pokémon is what inspired the name Moltres.

data.name: Galarian Zapdos
data.flavorText: One kick from its powerful legs will pulverize a dump truck. Supposedly, this Pokémon runs through the mountains at over 180 mph.

data.name: Galarian Slowpoke
data.flavorText: Because Galarian Slowpoke eat the seeds of a plant that grows only in Galar, their tails have developed a spicy flavor.

data.name: Light Toxtricity
data.flavorText: When this Pokémon sounds as if it's strumming a guitar, it's actually clawing at the protrusions on its chest to generate electricity.

data.name: Oricorio
data.flavorText: This Oricorio has drunk red nectar. If its Trainer gives the wrong order, this passionate Pokémon becomes fiercely angry.

data.name: Pyukumuku
data.flavorText: It's covered in a slime that keeps its skin moist, allowing it to stay on land for days without drying up.

data.name: Deoxys
data.flavorText: DNA from a space virus mutated and became a Pokémon. It appears where auroras are seen.

data.name: Latias
data.flavorText: It can telepathically communicate with people. It changes its appearance using its down that refracts light.

data.name: Tepig
data.flavorText: It loves to eat roasted berries, but sometimes it gets too excited and burns them to a crisp.

data.name: Blitzle
data.flavorText: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.

data.name: Espeon
data.flavorText: It unleashes psychic power from the orb on its forehead. When its power is exhausted, the orb grows dull and dark.

data.name: Eevee
data.flavorText: Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokémon conceals many different possible evolutions.

data.name: Moltres
data.flavorText: It's one of the legendary bird Pokémon. When Moltres flaps its flaming wings, they glimmer with a dazzling red glow.

data.name: Lucario
data.flavorText: It controls waves known as auras, which are powerful enough to pulverize huge rocks. It uses these waves to take down its prey.

data.name: Liepard
data.flavorText: Don't be fooled by its gorgeous fur and elegant figure. This is a moody and vicious Pokémon.

data.name: Bibarel
data.flavorText: It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.

data.name: Flapple
data.flavorText: It flies on wings of apple skin and spits a powerful acid. It can also change its shape into that of an apple.

data.name: Eevee
data.flavorText: Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokémon conceals many different possible evolutions.

data.name: Leafeon
data.flavorText: This Pokémon's tail is blade sharp, with a fantastic cutting edge that can slice right though large trees.

data.name: Glaceon
data.flavorText: The coldness emanating from Glaceon causes powdery snow to form, making it quite a popular Pokémon at ski resorts.

data.name: Galarian Obstagoon
data.flavorText: It evolved after experiencing numerous fights. While crossing its arms, it lets out a shout that would make any opponent flinch.

data.name: Rowlet
data.flavorText: Flies noiselessly on delicate wings. It has mastered the art of deftly launching dagger-sharp feathers from those same wings.

data.name: Cyndaquil
data.flavorText: Hails from the Johto region. Though usually curled into a ball due to its timid disposition, it harbors tremendous firepower.

data.name: Oshawott
data.flavorText: This Pokémon from the Unova region uses the shell on its belly as a weapon to cut down its foes. Thus, I've conferred upon this shell the name “scalchop.”

data.name: Special Delivery Bidoof
data.flavorText: It constantly gnaws on logs and rocks to whittle down its front teeth. It nests alongside water.

data.name: Hisuian Basculegion
data.flavorText: Clads itself in the souls of comrades that perished before fulfilling their goals of journeying upstream. No other species throughout all Hisui's rivers is Basculegion's equal.

data.name: Wyrdeer
data.flavorText: The black orbs shine with an uncanny light when the Pokémon is erecting invisible barriers. The fur shed from its beard retains heat well and is a highly useful material for winter clothing.

data.name: Hisuian Samurott
data.flavorText: Hard of heart and deft of blade, this rare form of Samurott is a product of the Pokémon's evolution in the region of Hisui. Its turbulent blows crash into foes like ceaseless pounding waves.

data.name: Magnezone
data.flavorText: Some say that Magnezone receives signals from space via the antenna on its head and that it's being controlled by some mysterious being.

data.name: Toxel
data.flavorText: It manipulates the chemical makeup of its poison to produce electricity. The voltage is weak, but it can cause a tingling paralysis.

data.name: Oricorio
data.flavorText: This Oricorio has sipped purple nectar. Some dancers use its graceful, elegant dancing as inspiration.

data.name: Sylveon
data.flavorText: There's a Galarian fairy tale that describes a beautiful Sylveon vanquishing a dreadful dragon Pokémon.

data.name: Eevee
data.flavorText: Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokémon conceals many different possible evolutions.

data.name: Radiant Eevee
data.flavorText: It has the ability to alter the composition of its body to suit its surrounding environment.

data.name: Bulbasaur
data.flavorText: There is a plant seed on its back right from the day this Pokémon is born. The seed slowly grows larger.

data.name: Charmander
data.flavorText: It has a preference for hot things. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

data.name: Squirtle
data.flavorText: When it retracts its long neck into its shell, it squirts out water with vigorous force.

data.name: Pikachu
data.flavorText: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy

data.name: Pikachu
data.flavorText: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

data.name: Finneon
data.flavorText: It lures in prey with its shining tail fins. It stays near the surface during the day and moves to the depths when night falls.

data.name: Gengar
data.flavorText: On the night of a full moon, if shadows move on their own and laugh, it must be Gengar's doing.

data.name: Comfey
data.flavorText: Comfey picks flowers with its vine and decorates itself with them. For some reason, flowers won't wither once they're attached to a Comfey.

data.name: Machamp
data.flavorText: It quickly swings its four arms to rock its opponents with ceaseless punches and chops from all angles.

data.name: Scorbunny
data.flavorText: It has special pads on the backs of its feet, and one on its nose. Once it's raring to fight, these pads radiate tremendous heat.

data.name: Croagunk
data.flavorText: Once diluted, its poison becomes medicinal. This Pokémon came into popularity after a pharmaceutical company chose it as a mascot.

data.name: Weavile
data.flavorText: They attack their quarry in packs. Prey as large as Mamoswine easily fall to the teamwork of a group of Weavile.

data.name: Regigigas
data.flavorText: There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.

data.name: Sunflora
data.flavorText: It gets energy from warm sunlight and is known for its habit of moving in pursuit of it.

data.name: Rapidash
data.flavorText: This Pokémon can be seen galloping through fields at speeds of up to 150 mph, its fiery mane fluttering in the wind.

data.name: Kirlia
data.flavorText: If its Trainer becomes happy, it overflows with energy, dancing joyously while spinning about.

data.name: Archeops
data.flavorText: It needs a running start to take off. If Archeops wants to fly, it first needs to run nearly 25 mph, building speed over a course of about 2.5 miles.

data.name: Hisuian Basculin
data.flavorText: Though it differs from other Basculin in several respects, including demeanor - this one is gentle - I have categorized it as a regional form given the vast array of shared qualities.

data.name: Cranidos
data.flavorText: Its hard skull is its distinguishing feature. It snapped trees by headbutting them, and then it fed on their ripe berries.

data.name: Manaphy
data.flavorText: It starts life with a wondrous power that permits it to bond with any kind of Pokémon.

data.name: Togetic
data.flavorText: They say that it will appear before kindhearted, caring people and shower them with happiness.

data.name: Rillaboom
data.flavorText: The one with the best drumming techniques becomes the boss of the troop. It has a gentle disposition and values harmony among its group.

data.name: Cinderace
data.flavorText: It's skilled at both offense and defense, and it gets pumped up when cheered on. But if it starts showboating, it could put itself in a tough spot.

data.name: Inteleon
data.flavorText: Its nictitating membranes let it pick out foes' weak points so it can precisely blast them with water that shoots from its fingertips at Mach 3.

data.name: Special Delivery Charizard
data.flavorText: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.

data.name: Galarian Articuno
data.flavorText: Known as Articuno, this Pokémon fires beams that can immobilize opponents as if they had been frozen solid.

data.name: Greninja
data.flavorText: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two.

data.name: Galarian Zapdos
data.flavorText: One kick from its powerful legs will pulverize a dump truck. Supposedly, this Pokémon runs through the mountains at over 180 mph.

data.name: Galarian Moltres
data.flavorText: The sinister aura that blazes like molten fire around this Pokémon is what inspired the name Moltres.

data.name: Bulbasaur
data.flavorText: There is a plant seed on its back right from the day this Pokémon is born. The seed slowly grows larger.

data.name: Arcanine
data.flavorText: The sight of it running over 6,200 miles in a single day and night has captivated many people.
